<HEADLINE> 39 Die of Diseases in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 3 (Xinhua) -- An outbreak of gastro-enteritis,
influenza and fever has claimed at least 39 lives in Dolakha and
Dhanusa districts in central Nepal, sources said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A medical team has been sent to Dolakha district, where at
least 15 people have died. Now the diseases have been brought
under control.
</P>
<P>
In Dhanusa district, 24 people have died and 2,660 others are
affected. A medical team has been dispatched there, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
More than 228 persons in 15 districts of Nepal had died of
gastro-enteritis, typhoid, and fever during the summer season.
</P>
<P>
Contaminated drinking water, lack of medicine and food, and
lack of awareness are blamed for the outbreak of the diseases.
</P>
</TEXT>
