<HEADLINE> Kiriyenko Confident About Russia's Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Sergei
Kiriyenko expressed his confidence in the country's economic
situation Wednesday, just before his departure for France.
</P>
<P>
"I am absolutely confident that the situation is under
control. All government and Central Bank staff know their
responsibilities and carry them out excellently," the prime
minister told reporters.
</P>
<P>
Kiriyenko was speaking as Russia struggled to weather a
financial crisis which tumbled the stock market and spread panic
among investors during the past week.
</P>
<P>
His two-day visit to France is his first official trip overseas
since he took office in April.
</P>
<P>
Kiriyenko said he would be provided with urgent information and
was leaving with calmness and confidence.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that "investors' rights must be protected."
