<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Namibia Halts Wild Animal Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Namibian government has
indefinitely halted the export of live wild animals, South
African Press Association (SAPA) reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Namibian Deputy Minister of Environment and Tourism Nangolo
Ithete said in a statement Tuesday that no further export permits
would be issued pending a policy review, according to SAPA.
</P>
<P>
Ithete said that the decision was meant to encourage local
processing, to add value to the country's wildlife resources and
to protect endemic wildlife.
</P>
<P>
The embargo will not affect the export of exotic species of
wild birds or exports of live animals which are in line with a
recognized conservation program.
</P>
<P>
All wildlife export permits issued before Tuesday remain
valid, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
