<HEADLINE> Tonle Sap Lake Named World Biosphere Reserve </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, June 3 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony marking the handing
over of a certificate to the Royal Government of Cambodia for the
newly world accredited Tonle Sap Biosphere Reserve was held
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony, at the Council of Ministers, was attended by
H.E. Sok An, co-minister of the Council, H.E. Mok Mareth, minister
of environment, H.E. Tao Seng Hour, United Nations Educational,
Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO) representative to
Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia's Tonle Sap Lake was officially included by UNESCO in
the List of the World Network of Biosphere Reserves in October,
1997.
</P>
<P>
Tonle Sap Biosphere Reserve is delineated into three
zones: core areas, the buffer zone and the transition zone.
</P>
<P>
Lefevre told the ceremony it took several years of work to
officially create the Tonle Sap Biosphere Reserve.
</P>
<P>
He said the Tonle Sap is the heart and breath of the economy,
culture and society of Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Its unique biodiversity and ecological characteristics, its
richness in natural resources and impressive natural beauty
deserves every effort from local, national and also international
bodies to make it a sustainable future, said Lefevre.
</P>
<P>
"Today, the importance of the Tonle Sap is not only recognized
in Cambodia but also by international communities as a whole,"
said the UNESCO representative. 
</P>
</TEXT>
