<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1630 GMT June 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN -- At least 70 people were killed and 300 others injured,
most of them seriously, in Germany's worst train accident in two
decades when a high speed train crashed Wednesday in a small
northern town.
</P>
<P>
Officials in charge of the emergency operation at the scene
said the number of people killed could rise to over 100.
(Germany-Train Crash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India's naval version of surface-to-air missile
"Trishul" was flight tested from an Indian naval ship in Cochin
port of southwestern India Wednesday. (India-Missile)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- President Bill Clinton proposed Wednesday the
renewal of China's normal trade relations. The U.S. president is
obliged by law to proposed by June 3 if China's most-favored
nation trade statues should be renewed.
</P>
<P>
China's MFN trade status has been renewed annually in recent
years. U.S. Congress has 30 days to endorse or reject the
proposal. (US-China-MFN)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KATHMANDU -- An outbreak of gastro-enteritis, influenza and
fever has claimed at least 39 lives in Dolakha and Dhanusa
districts in central Nepal, sources said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A medical team has been sent to Dolakha district, where at
least 15 people have died. Now the diseases have been brought
under control. (Nepal-Disease-Death) 
</P>
