<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Special Representative of
U.N. Secretary-General in Angola Alioune Blondin Bere has decided
to postpone his visit to the Headquarters of the United Nations,
U.N. spokesman Fred Eckhard said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Bere originally planned to come to the United Nations and brief
the Security Council on the latest situation in Angola on Friday.
</P>
