Nations until mid June," Eckhard said.
</P>
<P>
"The Security Council will consider the next steps to take
after briefed by the Special Representative," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The completion of the peace process in Angola has been stalled
mainly by delays in extension of Government authority to towns
held by the National Union for the Total Independence of Angola
(UNITA).
</P>
<P>
The Security Council of the United Nations has warned that it
will consider and impose additional sanctions against UNITA if it
refuses to fulfill all the obligations under the Lusaka Protocol.
