<HEADLINE> France Provides Financial Aid to Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The French government agreed
Wednesday to provide 240 million Zimbabwean Dollars (13 million
U.S. Dollars) to help improve Zimbabwe's infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
A financial protocol was signed by Zimbabwean Finance Minister
Herbert Murerwa and French Ambassador to Zimbabwe Hadelin de la
Tour-du-pin.
</P>
<P>
The protocol will enable Zimbabwe to realise urgent
infrastructure works in water and telecommunications sectors,
Tour-du-pin said.
</P>
<P>
This is the eighth protocol between France and Zimbabwe since
the latter's independence in 1980.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador said that France's total financial aid to
Zimbabwe granted so far amounts to about 5.5 billion Zimbabwean
Dollars (300 million U.S. Dollars).
</P>
<P>
"This protocol is a mixed credit facility consisting of two
equal parts of concessional and commercial loans to be repaid in
twenty and five years respectively," he said. 
</P>
