Russia and ASEAN share view on the situation in the Asian-Pacific
region and the whole world.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting the officials from ASEAN countries expressed
concern about the nuclear tests in India and Pakistan and said
they are closely watching the ongoing meeting of the five U.N.
permanent members who have gathered in Geneva to discuss the
situation in South Asia.
</P>
<P>
According to Karasin, the ASEAN position is that Russia, China,
the United States and Japan are the guarantors of security in the
Asian-Pacific region and should become a "political vanguard to
make the countries in the region feel secure."
</P>
<P>
Karasin said earlier today, Russia stated its intention to
expand economic cooperation with the APR countries. The Russian
Federation should not confine its ties only to the West. Russia
must advance its companies and banks to this region because
Russia's future is in the Asian-Pacific region, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
In his message to the participants of the meeting Russian
Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov said that the meeting has
activated a new mechanism of practical cooperation between Russia
and ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that the realization of the partnership
between Russia and ASEAN will benefit both Moscow and ASEAN
members.  
