<HEADLINE> Audi Offers to Buy UK's Cosworth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Germany's carmaker Audi has made an
offer to buy British engine company Cosworth from its parent
company Vickers, a spokesman of Audi announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Audi, a subsidiary of Germany's largest carmaker Volkswagen,
had signed a letter of intent to buy Cosworth for 120 million
British pounds (197 million U.S. dollars), the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
However, the deal was still dependent on Volkswagen's bid to
take over the British luxury car manufacturer Rolls-Royce, which
is also owned by Vickers.
</P>
<P>
Volkswagen has pledged 430 million pounds (706 million dollars)
to buy Rolls-Royce, outbidding the 340 million pounds (558 million
dollars) offered by its German rival suitor BMW. Audi's bid for
Cosworth is meant to further strengthen Volkswagen's hand.
</P>
<P>
But a group of British and U.S. car enthusiasts are still
planning to table a last-minute bid to outgun both of the German
rivals.
</P>
<P>
Vickers is due to hold a shareholders' assembly on Friday to
vote on the three bids.  
</P>
