<HEADLINE> Seles Topples Hingis for French Open Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Monica Seles toppled top-seeded
Martina Hingis 6-3, 6-2 to enter the French Open final here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav-born American, playing two weeks after her
father's death, outpowered her Swiss rival with fast serves and
strong baseline strokes as Hingis committed a string of unforced
errors.
</P>
<P>
With her first ever win over Hingis, Seles advances to her
first Grand Slam final since the 1996 U.S. Open. 
