<HEADLINE> China Supports Cooperation in APEC Telecom, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 4 (Xinhua) -- A high-ranking Chinese minister
has said that China supports the strengthened cooperation among
APEC member economies to realize the common development and
prosperity of the telecommunication and information sector in the
region.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Minister of Information Industry Wu Jichuan made the
remark in his speech at a plenary session Thursday of the Third
APEC Ministerial Meeting on the Telecommunication and Information
Industry, which began Wednesday with an aim to rally joint efforts
to realize the goal of creating an Asia-Pacific Information
Society.
</P>
<P>
It will be of strategic significance for the member economies
to further strengthen international cooperation and make full use
of the achievement in rapidly developing telecommunication and
information technologies while adopting their respective
development policies and objectives and relying mainly on their
own efforts, he said.
</P>
<P>
In order to meet the advent of the information society, he
said, the APEC ministers responsible for telecommunications and
information industry should closely follow the development trend
of information technology in the 21st century in the region,
formulate strategies and solve the problems brought about by
technological progress.
</P>
<P>
He proposed to encourage and support APEC members in their
joint efforts to develop technical and service standards for
broadband multi-media communications, to work together to develop
international standards and coordinated policies in the area of
E-commerce, and to carry out studies on equitable, mutually
beneficial, and cost-based tariff and settlement arrangements,
including those involved in Internet service provision.
</P>
<P>
He also told the session that China has mapped out the
development objectives for telecommunications and information
industry for the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, he said, in the year 2000 China will have a
high-rate chessboard-structured broadband fiber-optic cable
network across the whole country and the annual sales in the
information and software industries will hit 54 billion U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Third APEC Ministerial Meeting on the Telecommunications
and Information Industry will end on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
