<HEADLINE> U.S. Soccer Team Prepares for France World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. World Cup soccer team
will leave for France tonight following a last training session
Wednesday on a softball field in Central Park of New York.
</P>
<P>
The players jogged around the field and did some light
stretching exercises during a 30-minute workout.
</P>
<P>
The team will arrive in Paris on Friday, then will either fly
or ride the bus to Lyon. They start their opener in Paris on June
15 against three-time World Cup champions Germany.
</P>
<P>
The squad will then fight against Iran on June 21 in Lyon and
wind up its first round against Yugoslavia on June in Nantes.
</P>
<P>
"We know we're going over there with three tough games just to
get out of the first round," Forward Roy Wegerle said. "We have
nothing to fear against these teams. It's going to be no walk in
the park for these teams playing us, too."
</P>
<P>
Eighteen of the 22 players trained in the afternoon work out.
The team hopes to finish a better place then its 14th ranking in
the previous World Cup. The team has a record of nine wins, three
losses and five draws since September 7, and has outscored its
opponents 23-11 over the stretch.
</P>
<P>
"Anything can happen in soccer," said the 37-year-old Thomas
Dooley, the team's captain and the oldest player. "We hope to have
a nice surprise for someone over there." 
</P>
</TEXT>
