<DOCNO> XIE19980604.0092 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ousting of S. Leone Junta A Victory for Africa: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OUAGADOUGOU, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The successful ousting of the
illegal military junta in Sierra Leone was described as a major
victory to Africa at the 68th ordinary session of the council of
ministers of the Organization of African Unity which opened here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In a statement delivered to the opening ceremony of the
council session Thursday morning, OAU Secretary-General Salim
Ahmed Salim said that Africa displayed remarkable cohesion and
decisiveness in dealing with the crisis that erupt in Sierra
Leone following the coup d'etat by a military junta in May last
year.
</P>
<P>
"This swift, decisive and unequivocal reaction by our
continental organization against the coup and the crucial role
played subsequently by ECOWAS (Economic Community of West African
States) and ECOMOG (west African peace keeping force), on behalf
of the continent, led to the early restoration of the
democratically elected government of Sierra Leone," he said.
</P>
<P>
This strengthened Africa's will and commitment to stand in
defense of democracy in the continent, he added.
</P>
<P>
"The position of principle which Africa took in the case of
Sierra Leone marked the continued determination of the continent
to ensure that democracy gains root in the continent," he said,
adding that more needs to be done to ensure that the people's
rights are guaranteed, promoted and protected.
</P>
<P>
The experience of Sierra Leone has clearly demonstrated that
there are real prospects for success in overcoming crisis
situations, he said.
</P>
<P>
"This is especially pertinent as we are still confronted with
the daunting challenge of seeking durable peace in various parts
of the continent," he concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
