good deal," he would move forward regardless of opposition inside
his own coalition, which is splitting over the redeployment amid
pressure from the United States for an early decision.
</P>
<P>
The latest draft of the U.S. proposal was published for the
first time on Israeli newspaper Haaretz Thursday. Under the plan,
Israel will carry out a three-stage further redeployment over a
period of 12 weeks.
</P>
<P>
Israel Radio reported Thursday that U.S. peace envoy Dennis
Ross, who presented the plan to both the Israeli and Palestinian
sides last Wednesday, was holding talks in London with Mahmoud
Abbas (Abu Mazen), Palestinian National Authority deputy head, and
Palestinian Legislative Council Speaker Ahmed Qureia (Abu Ala) on
the proposal.
</P>
<P>
Weizman also met with an Israeli peace group Peace Now
delegation before he left for Cairo, Egypt. 
