students to file an urgent court action challenging Hill's
decision, the Zimbabwe News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
He said the vice-chancellor is empowered by the university act
to prohibit a group of students from attending lessons, but has
no powers to close down the institution.
</P>
<P>
"He can suspend any member of staff and prohibit students from
attending class, but the actual closing of the university is not
provided for in the act," Chihota said.
</P>
<P>
He said punishing all the students, including those who never
participated in the demonstration, was uncalled for.
</P>
<P>
Hill closed down the university Tuesday followin the
destruction of property by students demonstrating against alleged
corruption in government and demanding increased grants and
loans.
</P>
<P>
In the demonstrations between Thursday, last week and Monday,
this week, the students carried placards urging President Robert
Mugabe to resign. 
