<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arafat in Yemen for Preparation of Arab Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian President Yasser Arafat
arrived here Thursday to brief Yemeni President Ali Abdullah Saleh
on his current regional tour for pushing the convocation of an
Arab summit aimed at reviving the deadlocked peace process.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival from Omani capital Muscat, Arafat told the
Yemeni news agency that he would keep Saleh informed about the
developments of the peace process and the obstacles facing it. He
said he would listen to Saleh's advices.
</P>
<P>
Arafat's visit to Yemen comes within the framework of the
Palestinian drive to call for an expanded Arab summit.
</P>
<P>
He has visited Egypt, Saudi Arabia, Morocco, the United Arab
Emirates and Oman and held talks with leaders of the Arab
countries on the issue.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Palestinian Cabinet Secretary Tayeb Abdel Rahim has
disclosed that Arafat will visit Jordan for talks with Jordanian
King Hussein in the same context.
</P>
<P>
For several months, the Palestinians have been urging holding
an Arab summit to rally support for their stance in the peace
negotiations with Israel and to secure a common strategy to
confront the intransigent policies of the Israeli government.
</P>
