<HEADLINE> Nanjing Airport Admitted to International Airports Council </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Lukou Airport in this capital of
east China's Jiangsu Province today became a member of the
International Airports Council, a worldwide association
headquartered in Geneva in Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
The council has so far admitted six Chinese airports as
members. The five others are the Beijing Capital Airport, the
Hongqiao International Airport in Shanghai, the Baiyun Airport in
Guangzhou, the Huangtian Airport in Shenzhen and the airport in
Xiamen.
</P>
<P>
The council aims to build a safe and effective air traffic
system by enhancing the cooperation between airports, governments,
airlines and plane manufacturers worldwide.
</P>
<P>
The council has six committees and 451 members in 150 countries
and regions. 
</P>
