</P>
<P>
-- The F.D.A. gave a California company, Vaxgen, approval to
conduct the world's first full-scale test of a vaccine to prevent
infection with the virus that causes AIDS. The vaccine was found
to be safe in previous testing and induced the production of
anti-bodies in more than 99 percent of the vaccinated
participants, the company said. The major question the new tests
aim to answer is how effective the vaccine will be in protecting
people exposed to H.I.V. because of high-risk sexual practices or
drug use.
</P>
