renewing trade privileges for China and pressing for quick
ratification of the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty, linking both
issues to his struggle to defuse a nuclear arms race in South Asia.
</P>
<P>
-- Nearly 15 years after he was first hunted by U.S. law
enforcement, a Palestinian alleged to have been among the most
skillful Middle East terrorists of the 1980s was secretly bundled
out of Egypt and flown to the United States yesterday to face
charges in a federal court.
</P>
<P>
The Wall Street Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- Intel's shares fell 4.8 percent amid new worries about the
strength of the PC market. Some analysts cut earnings estimates
and rumors spread that Intel would warn second-quarter earnings
will be lower than expected. Intel also is expected to cut prices
on its Pentium II chips this weekend. Separately, the
Semiconductor Industry Association predicted chip-industry revenue
will shrink 1.8 percent in 1998.
</P>
<P>
USA Today:
</P>
