<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets With Luxembourg PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC), met with Prime
Minister Jean-Claude Juncker of Luxembourg and his party here
today.
</P>
<P>
Li and Juncker said that they were delighted to meet again
three months after Li's visit to Luxembourg last February.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China had witnessed new changes after Juncker's
previous China visit. "In the two decades since its reform and
opening-up drive, China has made achievements in socio-economic
development with marked improvements in the people's life and
enhanced national strength," Li said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the experience of China's progress can be summed
up as the proper handling of the relationship between reform,
development and stability.
</P>
<P>
"Without stability, China, a country with a population of 1.2
billion, could not do anything. Stability is the prerequisite for
refrom and development. And only under stable conditions can the
state be engaged in development and people live in peace and work
in contentment," Li noted.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China now has three tasks ahead. "The first is to
retain the development momentum for China's national economy; the
second is to strengthen reform; and the third to enhance
democratic and legal construction," he said, adding that China is
confident and capable of tackling all difficulties and problems
occurring in the development process.
</P>
<P>
Li told guests that China chooses the system of people's
congresses and the system of multi-party cooperation and political
consultation under the leadership of the Chinese Communist Party
(CPC). Both are suited to China's national conditions. Based on
the general principle put forward at the 15th CPC National
Congress to govern the country according to law, NPC will play its
due role in strengthening the law-making and relevant supervision
efforts so as to ensure the building of a socialist country ruled
by law, and guarantee and promote the smooth development of the
reform and opening-up drive.
</P>
<P>
Li highly evaluated the improved ties between China and the
European Union (EU). China highly values the role played by the EU
in global and regional affairs, and its unremitting efforts to
advance Sino-Europe relations, Li noted.
</P>
<P>
"In an increasingly multi-polarized world, China and Europe
have more common points in bilateral and multilateral fields," Li
said.
</P>
<P>
According to Li, the NPC has already formed regular contacts
and dialogue channels with the European parliament. Li said that
he hoped that such exchanges can be expanded and also expressed
particular appreciation for the contribution made by Juncker for
furthering Sino-EU ties.
</P>
<P>
Juncker told Li that his visit to Luxembourg early this year
played an important role in furthering Sino-Luxembourg and Sino-EU
ties. He said that his state will, as usual, made efforts to
enhance such ties. He said it can be predicted that a more
enlarged and unified EU and a more powerful China will see new
bilateral cooperation at a new phase. 
</P>
