<HEADLINE> Xiamen Maintains High Air Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Xiamen's Deputy Mayor Zhao Keming
announced today that the city has recorded first-grade air
quality in the national classification for the ninth year running
this year.
</P>
<P>
The average indices of sulphur dioxide, nitrogen and oxygen
compounds and suspended particles are all up to the
national standards, according to the city's 1997
environmental quality bulletin, which was released today.
</P>
<P>
Xiamen, a coastal city in eastern Fujian Province, was cited as
a model of environmental protection by the State Bureau of
Environmental Protection in November 1997.
</P>
<P>
The 1997 environmental quality bulletin also indicates the
comprehensive environmental improvements made by the city,
compared with the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 97.02 percent of Xiamen's drinking water
sources have reached the required quality level, the noise level
has decreased, and imported waste has been brought under effective
control. 
</P>
