Australia Genta Holmes Hawkins signed an agreement on the
extension here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It is the third time that the pact, which was first signed in
1967, has been extended. It will now operate until November 2008,
Defense Minister Ian McLachlan said in a statement available here.
</P>
<P>
The extension reflects the value of the Pine Gap facility to
both countries, McLachlan said.
</P>
<P>
Pine Gap is an intelligence gathering facility in northern
Australia. 
