<HEADLINE> Intellectual Property Services Center Launched in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Intellectual Property
Services Center (IPSC) was launched here Thursday to help Hong
Kong companies and individuals capitalize on their invention
through patent registration.
</P>
<P>
The center was set up by the Hong Kong Productivity Council
(HKPC), responding to the objective set out by Chief Executive
Tung Chee Hwa in his 1997 Policy Address to develop Hong Kong into
an innovation center.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the center's opening ceremony, HKPC Executive
Director Thomas Tang said: "The ISPC will provide a comprehensive
range of services in patent search and patent registration. This
one-stop service will enable companies to shorten the
time-to-market for new products, enhancing their competitiveness."
</P>
<P>
Services offered range from patent search to assistance in
application of patents, industrial designs, trademarks and
copyright protection.
</P>
<P>
"In developing new products, industrialists often need to know
if such products or aspects of them have been developed or
patented by other manufacturers, locally or overseas. By having
on-line access to major databases worldwide on patents and other
intellectual property information, the center is well-positioned
to provide this service," Tang noted.
</P>
<P>
According to Dr. W. C. Keung, HKPC director in charge of the
Information Technology and Services Branch, to enhance efficiency,
the center also has a Consultation clinic to help assess the
potential of a product or technology in obtaining patent
registration before commencing application procedures.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the center is in line with HKPC's overall
initiative to promote invention, innovation, information and
industrialization. The council is a statutory body established in
1967 to promote productivity excellence in industries.
</P>
<P>
The council's efforts to promote innovation and invention
included the recent establishment of the Product Development and
Innovation Institute and the upcoming Chinese International
Invention Expo '98 to be held in late November. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
