<HEADLINE> Qingdao Zone Utilizes More Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 4 (Xinhua) -- A major development zone in Qingdao,
a coastal city of east China's Shandong Province, reported a
significant increase in the amount of overseas investment in the
first four months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The Qingdao Economic and Technology Development Zone approved
43 overseas-funded projects between January and April, with total
investment hitting 56 million US dollars-worth, a surge of 186
percent over the corresponding period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics also show that contracted and paid-in
overseas investment in the zone rocketed 182 and 52 percent,
respectively, from a year ago. An analysis indicates that
investment from Europe and the Americas jumped more than 60
percent.
</P>
<P>
The lingering Asian financial crisis has produced some negative
impacts on Shandong's economy and trade, but investment in the
Qingdao zone by overseas consortiums has continued to rise, a zone
official said.
</P>
<P>
Currently, companies from 44 countries and regions have come to
investe in the development zone, with total investment adding up
to 2.28 billion US dollars, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, large enterprises from 22 Chinese provinces and
municipalities have also invested in the zone six billion yuan
(720 million US dollars) in contracted value. 
</P>
