<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Thursday on thin trading as
investors traded on a cautious note.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index dropped
7.75 points to 518.61, the all-share Emas Index lost 1.63 points
to 132.85, the Industrial Index shed 6.97 points to 1,015.84 and
the Second Board Index lost 0.92 of a point to 110.27.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers by 354 to 187 while 161 counters
were unchanged and 218 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover dropped to 98.388 million shares valued at
241.041 million ringgit (about 61.023 million U.S. dollars) from
126.114 million shares worth 267.434 million ringgit (about 67.704
million U.S. dollars) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The main board volume decreased to 90.887 million shares valued
at 229.016 million ringgit (about 57.978 million U.S. dollars)
from Wednesday's 115.654 million shares worth 251.621 million
ringgit (about 63.701 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the second board declined to 7.501 million shares
valued at 12.025 million ringgit (about 3.044 million U.S.
dollars) from 10.460 million shares worth 15.812 million ringgit
(about 4.003 million U.S. dollars) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals shrank to 878,333 shares valued at 4.043
million ringgit (about 1.023 million U.S. dollars) from 5.112
million shares valued at 18.607 million ringgit (about 4.71
million U.S. dollars) on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
