<HEADLINE> HK Housing Authority Publishes 1st Corporate Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Housing Authority (HA) of the
 Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) released Thursday
its first Corporate Plan which sets out the ways to meet new
challenges as it heads for the next millennium.
</P>
<P>
The Corporate Plan for 1998/99 was tabled at the HA Annual
Special Meeting. It outlines key strategies and new initiatives of
the Authority drawn up with reference to the approved business
plans, the HA Annual Budget as well as the pledges and commitments
put forward by the Government in the 1997 Policy Address.
</P>
<P>
"Through the Corporate Plan, we are communicating our vision
and mission to the community and accounting for our performance,"
an HA spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The new challenges faced by the HA include strong demand for
public housing, growing aspirations for home ownership, high
expectations of services, the call for close partnership with the
private sector and the need to achieve optimal cost-effectiveness
and operational efficiency within the Housing Department.
</P>
<P>
"We have devised in the Corporate Plan ways to accomplish a
wide range of organizational goals, which includes lifting flat
production, reducing waiting time, enhancing home ownership and
helping people in genuine need," the spokesman noted. 
</P>
