<HEADLINE> Shanghai's May Foreign Exchange Turnover Up Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Turnover on the Shanghai Foreign
Exchange Trading System totaled 4.345 billion US dollars-worth in
May, up three percent from April.
</P>
<P>
The total amount includes 4.08 billion US dollars, 2.3 billion
Hong Kong dollars and 5.325 billion Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
The exchange rate of the US dollar rose slightly in May, from
one dollar to 8.2779 yuan on April 30 to one dollar to 8.2793 yuan
on May 29, the last trading session of the month.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong dollar, which is pegged to the US currency, also
edged up last month. It was traded at 1.0687 yuan at the end of
April, but rose to 1.0692 yuan by the end of May.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese yen's exchange rate against the Chinese currency
continued to decline in May. It was quoted at 100 yen to 6.2661
yuan at the end of April, but dropped to 5.9681 yuan at the end of
May. 
</P>
