<HEADLINE> Philippine Caltex to Raise Oil Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Caltex, one of the three major
players in the Philippine oil industry, will raise the prices of
unleaded, premium and diesel products midnight Thursday,
Philippine News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Caltex dealers as saying that unleaded
gasoline, premium gasoline and diesel will go up by an average of
40 centavos to 11.69 pesos (0.3 U.S. dollars), 12.04 pesos (0.31
dollars) and 8.35 pesos (0.21 dollars) a liter.
</P>
<P>
Unioil and Flying V, two of the new entrants in the retail oil
marketing, have also adjusted their new prices Thursday after
Shell Philippines raised its prices Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Industry sources believed that the recent hike in crude cost
and the depreciation of the peso against the dollar caused the
increases in oil prices.
</P>
<P>
The exchange rate between the peso and the dollar weakened by
about 1.7 percent to 39.098 pesos per dollar from the April
average of 38.43 pesos a dollar. 
