<HEADLINE> China's Industrial Sales Pick Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- China's industrial sales in April
hit a record high of the first four months of the year, with the
marketing ratio reaching 95.4 percent, slightly higher than in the
same period of 1997, according to the latest figures from the
State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Influenced by the Asian financial turmoil and sluggish market
demand, the country's industrial sales saw slow increases in the
first quarter of 1998, with the sales ratios all being below 95
percent.
</P>
<P>
The report indicates that 18 provinces, municipalities and
autonomous regions saw their industrial sales grow in April, and
Northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region's sales ratio in
the month was 7.48 percentage points higher than that of the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The statistics show that the country's accumulated industrial
sales ratio in the first four months reached 94.24 percent,
slightly lower than in the same period of 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
