<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wild Animals Reappear in Beijing Suburbs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Certain wild animals have
reappeared in the suburbs of Beijing, thanks to the municipal
government's efforts to promote environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Wu Jiwei, a local wild animal protection official, said here
today that Beijing launched the country's largest survey on the
distribution and species of wild animals in August 1997.
</P>
<P>
The wild animals found include swans, leopards, vultures,
hares, wild boars, deer, wolves, pheasants and snakes, he said.
</P>
<P>
In the western suburbs of Beijing people have found tracks of
wolves, wild boars and leopards in forested and
mountainous areas, according to the survey.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the survey shows that herds of deer and
badgers, and flocks of wild birds are living in other rural
suburbs of the city.  
</P>
</TEXT>
