<HEADLINE> Sydney Olympics to Offer Record Gold Awards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Sydney 2000 Olympics will offer
individual and team gold medals in a record 296 events, games
organisers said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Australian Olympic Committee president John Coates said 28
different sports had been incorporated into the program and the
total of medal events was 25 more than at the 1996 Atlanta
Olympics.
</P>
<P>
The official attributed the gold medals increase to the
introduction of new sports and disciplines which include women
events in sports such as modern pentathlon, water polo and
weightlifting.
</P>
<P>
Sydney organising committee president Michael Knight said 11
different sports at least would be contested on each of the 16
days of competition, with a maxium of 25 on the second and fourth
days.
</P>
<P>
At least 21 sports would be contested on the opening day of
competition, Saturday September 16, although soccer preliminaries
would start two days before the opening ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
