<HEADLINE> Substation Bombed in Western Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 4 (Xinhua) -- A substation was bombed in Western
Province of Sri Lanka Thursday morning, according to police here.
</P>
<P>
The destruction of the transformers by an unidentified person
or group was as serious as that by a recent explosion at
Wrellawatte in Yakkala, about 40 kilometers from Colombo.
Thursday's blasts occurred around 4:00 a.m., a senior police
official said.
</P>
<P>
Ceylon (Sri Lankan) Electricity Board officials estimated the
damage at around 500,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
There was an indication that the substation blasts were similar
to the telecom blasts which happened in May simultaneously, police
said.
</P>
<P>
There had been five bomb attacks at telephone exchanges in
Chenkaladi, Dehiwela, Kaliyapitiya, Kulitara and Nochchiyagama in
Sri Lanka last month.
</P>
<P>
It was said that the government views these incidents as acts
of sabotage by certain parties in a bid to damage the country's
economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
