<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Farmers in East China Builds Environmental Protection Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Farmers in Fujian Province, east
China, will build an environmental protection town that combines
economic development with a sound ecological system.
</P>
<P>
Pengkou Town covers 209 sq km and has 27,000 people. It has
been chosen by the Ministry of Agriculture as a "green food
production center".
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has decided to turn the town into an
environmental protection model, because of its forestry,
water, and agricultural resources.
</P>
<P>
The town will mainly be involved in the production of flowers,
fruit, vegetables, aquatic products and animal husbandry.
</P>
<P>
Only environment-friendly companies will be set up in the
town.
</P>
<P>
Construction is underway on some key projects like a forest
park and a 1,200-square-meter fairground.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
