<DOCNO> XIE19980604.0197 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US President's Decision on China's MFN Status is Wise: FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman
Zhu Bangzao said that US President Clinton has made a "wise
decision" when he informed the US Congress of renewing China's MFN
(most-favored- nation) status.
</P>
<P>
Asked to make the comment at a routine press conference here
today, Zhu noted that the mutual granting of MFN status between
China and the US is the basis of China-US economic relations and
trade, and it will facilitate the bilateral cooperation and
exchanges in the economic and trade field and bring about tangible
benefit to the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
It is therefore in the fundamental interest of the Chinese and
American peoples, added Zhu.
</P>
<P>
"What needs to be pointed out is that the annual review of
China's MFN status by the US side does not conduce to the
development of longterm, stable and normal economic relations and
trade between the two sides. We hope that the US side will abandon
this outmoded practice as soon as possible," Zhu said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
