<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France's GDP Grows 0.6 Percent in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The gross domestic product (GDP) of
France grew by 0.6 percent in the first quarter of this year
compared with the last quarter of 1997, said the official
statistics bureau INSEE on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
But the GDP growth in the first quarter was 1.9 percent
compared with the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Family consumption in the first three months also increased 0.6
percent as compared with the last quarter. This alone contributed
to the GDP growth by 0.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Manufactured products increased 1.2 percent following a 1.7
percent growth in the last quarter.
</P>
<P>
The import of industrial products increased by 2.9 percent,
more than 1.2 percent over the last quarter, while that of export
slowed down from 3.3 percent to 0.8 percent in the first quarter
of this year.
</P>
<P>
The import of other goods and services increased by 2.7
percent, while that of export in this field diminished to 0.7
percent from 1.9 percent in the last quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980604.0202 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Relief Operations Slowed by Rains in Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The relief operations in
earthquake-hit northern Afghanistan have been slowed by heavy
rains, reports reaching here from Kabul said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Heavy rains after the quake in Badakhshan and Takhar provinces
made it difficult and dangerous for planes to land, the reports
said.
</P>
<P>
Only a few helicopters made sorties to evaluate the extent of
damage and evacuate the injured on Wednesday, according to the
reports.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake measuring 7.1 on the Richter Scale occurred last
Saturday, in which at least 3,000 people were killed and about 50
villages destroyed.
</P>
<P>
It is difficult to assess the extent of casualties because
nobody has an exact figure for the total population of the
villages, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Coordinator for Afghanistan, Alfredo Witschi Cestari,
said Wednesday that aid agencies urgently need more cargo
helicopters and fuel to transport desperately needed relief goods
to Afghanistan's quake victims.
</P>
<P>
"We called upon everyone and anyone who can provide us with
helicopters to do so now," he said in a statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
