<HEADLINE> Hydroponic Flowers Popular in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 4 (Xinhua) -- More than 20 types of potted
plants have caught the attention of flower lovers at a flower
market in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
However, the plants are not potted in dirt but float freely in
water, with several fish swimming around them.
</P>
<P>
Such liquid nutriment was developed by a local bio-chemical
company that gets nutriments from animals and adds it to the
liquid mixture.
</P>
<P>
The flowers on display have been in the solution for
approximately six months and they are doing well. In fact, they
are doing better than those planted in soil.
</P>
<P>
People can just put the flowers in any glass container and add
new liquid every two weeks.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Flower Association says that the people here buy 300
million flowers annually, and 15 million pots of flowers were sold
last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
