Iqlim Toufah area, a stronghold for the Iranian-backed Hezbollah,
or Party of God.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah responded with heavy machineguns and rockets,
targeting Israeli posts in the mountainous area of the village of
Sujud, on the edge of the occupied zone.
</P>
<P>
Israel has been occupying a 1,200-square-kilometer border strip
in south Lebanon since 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting
its northern areas from Lebanese guerrillas cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanon's anti-occupation forces spearheaded by
Hezbollah have been fighting a guerrilla war trying to drive
Israeli occupation troops and their Lebanese militia allies out of
the occupied zone. 
