<HEADLINE> Canadian Aid For Chinese Training Program For Unemployed Women </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, June 4 (Xinhua) -- A training program for women
factory workers who had been laid off the job began recently in
Lanzhou, the capital of northwest China's Gansu Province, with
143,000 yuan in financial assistance from the Canadian government.
</P>
<P>
The city government will also provide 92,000 yuan for the
program, which will have 10 courses and provide training for 60
unemployed women each session, which lasts 40 days. The entire
program is running from May to October.
</P>
<P>
The women, who are between the ages of 20 and 40, will be given
textbooks and notebooks for free and will be taught basic skills
like marketing, household chores and cooking.
</P>
<P>
