<HEADLINE> Eastern Chinese City Starting River Purification Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Suzhou, in east China's Jiangsu
Province, is starting a water purification project that is
expected to cost 1.14 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The project includes building more sewage treatment plants,
laying underground sewage pipes, suburb-to-downtown water
diversion, and a new system to control the city's river network.
</P>
<P>
The government has already spent nearly 100 million yuan on
cleaning up the concentration of rivers in urban areas since 1996
to improve living conditions, the environment and tourism. 
</P>
</TEXT>
