<HEADLINE> Iran Keen to Expand Relations With Gulf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Iran has lashed out at the United
States for allegations of Iran's interference in Bahrain's
internal affairs, saying that it is keen to expand relations with
the Gulf states.
</P>
<P>
It is the interfering policies of the United States which have
always created tensions and crises among other countries, Iran's
official news agency IRNA Thursday quoted Foreign Ministry
spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi as saying on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
During the recent visit of Bahraini Emir Sheikh Isa bin Sulman
al-Khalifa to Washington, some U.S. officials blamed Iran for
interfering in Bahrain's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
During the past years, Manama accused Tehran of supporting
Bahrain's Shiite Muslims against the government. But Tehran has
always rejected such accusations.
</P>
<P>
Mohammadi said that Iran is keen to expand relations with the
neighboring countries, particularly the Persian Gulf states based
on mutual respect and good proximity, arguing that Iran has never
interfered in the internal affairs of other countries.
</P>
<P>
He noted that objectives behind the U.S. vain charges against
the regional independent nations are to explain its illegitimate
presence in the Persian Gulf and prevent proximity among the
regional nations.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also expressed the hope that relations between
Iran and other Gulf states will further develop in the light of
mutual cooperation and understandings. 
</P>
