<HEADLINE> China's Inner Mongolia Working For Better Ecological System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, June 4 (Xinhua) -- People in the Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region of China want to turn it into an
ecologically-sound area by the middle of next century, a regional
official said recently.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the goal will take 13 years to stop
environmental deterioration, and the second, building an
ecological system for sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
The region has increased environmental protection efforts on a
200,000-sq.km. area in land protection and building forests and
grassland.
</P>
<P>
Forests now cover 14.2 percent of the region, and one third of
the eroded and desertified land has been treated.
</P>
<P>
But the region also has about 800,000 square kilometers of
degraded land, and the degraded grassland area covers 38 million
hectares.
</P>
<P>
The regional government has taken steps to improve
environmental protection by returning land to use for husbandry,
planting trees and grass, and developing land protection
projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
