<HEADLINE> Indonesian Army Chief Urges Nation to Give </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Armed Forces (ABRI)
Commander Gen. Wiranto Wednesday once again called on the nation
to give the government the chance to resolve the economic crisis,
press reports said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Wiranto reiterated his support for President B.J. Habibie and
for the Reform and Development Cabinet which faces daunting tasks
to overcome the crisis and lead the reformation movement.
</P>
<P>
"ABRI has always supported the legitimate and constitutional
government recognized by the people. So, let's all together give
the government the chance to take various positive steps to solve
the problems facing this nation," said Wiranto, who is also
minister of defense and security.
</P>
<P>
His statement came amid calls for an extraordinary session of
the People's Consultative Assembly to elect a new leadership.
</P>
<P>
Habibie, who assumed the presidential office on May 21 after
the resignation of former president Soeharto, has promised fresh
elections next year to form a new assembly which will elect a new
president and a new vice president by the end of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Wiranto said demand for political reform must be tempered by
restraint, warning that radical demands could delay the country's
economic recovery.
</P>
<P>
"ABRI realizes that reform is not without limits. Reform cannot
steamroller the limits set by Pancasila ideology, the 1945
Constitution, nationalism and national unity and cohesion." he
said.
</P>
<P>
Pancasila is the five basic principles of the Republic of
Indonesia, which include belief in God, just and civilized
humanity, the unity of Indonesia, democracy guided by the wisdom
of representative deliberation, social justice for all
Indonesians.
</P>
<P>
Wiranto warned that activities that exceed the limits and get
out of control will obstruct the reform progress, "and they will
certainly have to face ABRI".
</P>
<P>
Referring to demands for an investigation into the source of
the former president Soeharto's family wealth, Wiranto called on
people to acknowledge Soeharto's achievements over the past three
decades and praised his wisdom in resignation when he did without
using the military to hold on to power. 
</P>
