</P>
<P>
Kohl, who arrived in Bologna, Italy, in the early evening,
boarded a plane back to Germany soon after his brief meeting with
Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi.
</P>
<P>
A high-speed train rammed into a road bridge when it was
travelling at 200 kmph in northern Germany Wednesday, killing at
least 100 people and injuring more than 100 others.
</P>
