<HEADLINE> Chilean Wine Exports Score a 40 Percent Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Chilean wine exports rose to 152
million U.S. dollars the first quarter this year, a 40 percent
increase over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
This year's exports would surpass 500 million U.S. dollars,
setting a new sales record, if the trend continued, according to
Chilean Association of Exportation of Wines.
</P>
<P>
The association said the increase was achieved when the
average price of Chilean wines rose 13.4 percent. Despite the
Asian financial crisis, exports to the region leaped about four
times during the first four months this year.
</P>
<P>
Bottled wine took the lead in the export growth, registering an
49.3 percent increase and valued at 130.70 million dollars. Bulk
wine exports increased 15.22 percent to a value of 21.88 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Chile, one of the world's top 10 wine exporters, sells wine to
around 70 countries. 
</P>
