<HEADLINE> Tourism Growth In Chinese Steel "Capital" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Anshan, China's iron and steel
industrial center in Liaoning Province that is known as the "Steel
Capital", is now drawing more visitors.
</P>
<P>
Although it is an important heavy industrial center, it also
has natural scenery and a religious culture.It had 710,000
domestic and overseas tourists, and earned 300 million yuan from
tourism in 1997, according to the provincial tourism department.
</P>
<P>
It still gives priority to iron and steel, but the local
government realizes the importance of tourism and is treating it
as a pillar industry for economic development, according to Geng
Jinghai, deputy director of the Anshan Tourism Bureau.
</P>
<P>
More private enterprises see rosy prospects for the city's
tourism and have spent at least 100 million yuan on it, Geng says.
</P>
<P>
The city had only 6 travel services in 1996, but had 20 by the
end of last year. 
