<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Greening Arid Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar is carrying out a greening
and environmental control project in 13 districts of the country's
three divisions of Sagaing, Mandalay and Magway which constitute
the arid zone of the country.
</P>
<P>
A new arid region greening department under the Ministry of
Forestry has been formed to implement the project which covers a
total area of 9,142,380 hectares. Of these, 1,529,879 hectares are
reserved forest, 3,281,135 hectares land outside them and
4,331,366 hectares cropping areas.
</P>
<P>
In addition to greening the region, the department also plans
to maintain ecology system, fulfill basic forest produce
requirements and carry out socio-economic development of the
rural people.
</P>
<P>
It has also laid down work programs to establish 14,175
hectares of nurseries annually, and conserve 40,500 hectares of
natural forest and another 40,500 hectares by grafting methods
annually.
</P>
<P>
It will also carry out works for greening some hills in the
tropical region in central Myanmar, green and lush special
greening project for watershed areas in Myingyan district and
greening of Mount Popa, according to the ministry.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar initiated the project of greening nine districts of
arid zone in central part of the country in the 1992-93 fiscal
year. More than 16 million trees were planted in an area of over
21,000 hectares covering 57 townships and 15 mountain ranges
between fiscal 1994-95 and 1996-97, of which 90 percent were
successful.
</P>
<P>
A 12-year project from 1997-98 to 2008-09 is under
implementation.
</P>
<P>
Forests cover about 51 percent of Myanmar's total land area.
</P>
</TEXT>
