<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belgium Beats Colombia in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Host Belgium beat Colombia 2-0 on
Wednesday in a soccer friendly that served as a tune-up for both
teams for the coming World Cup tournament.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Danny Boffin put the host side on the scoreboard in
the 16th minute when Marc Wilmots diverted a pass from within the
penalty area to the right where Luis Oliveira crossed the ball
back to the front of the Colombian goalmouth to set Boffin up for
his scoring header.
</P>
<P>
The Colombians could have equalized four minutes later when
Belgian goalkeeper Filip de Wilde misjudged a clearance kick on
the front line of his own area.
</P>
<P>
The scooped-up lob fell to waiting striker Faustino Asprilla
who headed the ball toward the unguarded goal but only wide.
</P>
<P>
The Belgians went two up in the 31st minute as Wilmots went it
alone with a 25-meter drive that just beat the fingertips of the
Colombian goalkeeper.
</P>
<P>
Asprilla had another chance early in the second half when there
was only the Belgian goalkeeper in between him and the opposing
goal. But he only saw his effort first blocked and then grabbed
by de Wilde.
</P>
<P>
Belgium next plays Paraguay on Saturday before leaving for
France where it plays the Netherlands, Mexico and South Korea in
group E preliminaries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
