<HEADLINE> FIA Cancels Indonesia Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The world auto racing ruling body FIA
Wednesday dropped the Rally of Indonesia from the 1998 race
calendar.
</P>
<P>
The FIA said in a statement it had withdrawn the September
rally from the schedule because of "the current situation in
Indonesia and difficulties with transportation of material for
competing teams."
</P>
<P>
The FIA said the schedule would be reduced from 14 to 13
events. It said it was too late to substitute a rally in China,
which was tentatively set for June 19-22.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia could return to the calendar in 1999, the FIA said.
</P>
