<DOCNO> XIE19980604.0313 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Supports Government Finance in Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank announced
Wednesday the approval of a 5 million U.S. dollar equivalent
interest-free credit to the government of Mongolia for a fiscal
technical assistance project.
</P>
<P>
The overall objective of this project is long-term
capacity-building and institutional development, and
sustainability is at the heart of the project. The project will
finance advisory services and training in government accounting,
treasury debt and cash management, auditing, management skills,
and related disciplines.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be provided by the International Development
Association (IDA), the World Bank's concessional lending arm for
developing countries.
</P>
<P>
This project is, in part, a follow-up to the first IDA
technical assistance credit, which financed specialist advisory
assistance and training in macroeconomic management and related
disciplines for staff of six core Mongolian economic agencies.
</P>
<P>
The IDA has provided technical assistance for development of
the government's macroeconomic management capability since 1992
and is currently supporting structural reforms in the banking and
enterprise sectors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
