<HEADLINE> IDB Supports Reform, Modernization Program in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank Wednesday announced the approval of an 80 million U.S. dollar
loan to the province of Mendoza, Argentina, to support its reform
program in the state.
</P>
<P>
The program includes public sector modernization and measures
to balance public revenue and expenditure. Steps will be taken to
improve spending efficiency and tax administration and to
modernize priority areas of the executive, legislative and
judicial branches.
</P>
<P>
About two thirds of the total resources for the project will be
dedicated to social development and reform of the health sector,
benefiting low income groups and increasing the coverage and
quality of basic services.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the IDB loan, local counterpart funds total 80
million dollars for the project.
</P>
<P>
The loan is the second made by the IDB directly to a province
in Argentina for the purpose of extending reforms already
undertaken at the national level. The first loan of this type was
provided to the province of Buenos Aires in December 1996.
</P>
</TEXT>
