<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Arrests Former PLO Officer for Bombing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The United States has arrested a
former Palestine Liberation Organization officer who has been
convicted for the bombing of a Hawaii-bound U.S. airliner in 1982,
Justice Department officials said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
They said Mohammad Rashid was scheduled to have an initial
appearance late in the day in U.S. District Court in Washington,
D.C..
</P>
<P>
Rashid was found involved in the 1982 bombing of a Pan American
airliner which exploded over Hawaii, killing a Japanese teenager
and injuring 15 other passengers. The plan managed to land safely.
</P>
<P>
He had been tracked around the world by the United States and
was arrested on an American tip-off at Athens international
airport in 1988. Greece put him on trial after rejecting an
extradition request from the United States.
</P>
<P>
Rashid was sentenced by a Greek court to 18 years in prison,
but was released at the end of 1996 by Greece for his "good
behavior." The move, however, enraged the United States, which had
been continuing its tracking.
</P>
<P>
The Justice Department officials declined to give details of
how Rashid was captured.
</P>
<P>
Rashid steadfastly has denied involvement in the bombing and
said he was the victim of mistaken identity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
